name: RFK Jr
summary: Robert F. Kennedy Jr., an outspoken advocate against vaccinations, has been nominated by President Trump to lead the Department of Health and Human Services (HHS). This move has raised concerns among HHS employees, who are considering leaving if Kennedy is confirmed. Kennedy's views on vaccines, fluoride, and drugs have been widely criticized by the scientific community. Opponents fear that his appointment could undermine public health efforts and exacerbate the spread of preventable diseases. One article even questions whether America's health can survive under Kennedy's leadership, while another predicts that his "MAHA" movement could radically transform public health. Kennedy's nomination has also drawn attention to his personal eccentricities, such as his claim that he had a dead worm in his brain. Critics have also pointed out that Kennedy has made disparaging remarks about Trump's diet in the past.

name: Haka
summary: Several news articles report on a disruption in the New Zealand parliament, where Maori lawmakers performed the traditional haka, a ceremonial dance. The haka was a form of protest against a proposed bill that would amend indigenous treaty rights. The protest led to the suspension of parliament. The haka, a powerful cultural symbol, was used to express the lawmakers' dismay and opposition to the bill, which they deemed detrimental to the rights of the Maori people.

name: Myer Christmas windows
summary: A planned pro-Palestinian protest targeting the unveiling of Christmas windows at Myer in Melbourne has been canceled. The decision came after widespread backlash and calls for the tradition to be preserved. People power is credited with reclaiming Christmas, as the protesters withdrew their plans to disrupt the 70-year-old tradition. The cancellation sparked debate, with some urging intervention from authorities to protect the beloved event. However, the protesters ultimately decided to drop their plans, leading to a large update on the scrapped Myer event. The cancellation had been dubbed a "Grinch" move, forcing the cancelation of the Melbourne Christmas tradition.

Additionally, an MSc student has been awarded the King Charles III Coronation Medal, and he and Kate Middleton attended a remembrance event together.

name: Tom Aspinall
summary: There is controversy surrounding UFC fighter Tom Aspinall, who claims he was excluded from the UFC 309 press conference. Some, including Barstool Sports, accuse Jon Jones of avoiding a fight with Aspinall, while Jones denies these claims, stating he was never scheduled to fight him. UFC President Dana White has confirmed that the winner of UFC 309, Jones, will fight Aspinall unless he retires. However, Jones has dismissed the idea, leading to criticism and accusations of him being a "fraud" and making excuses. Other fighters have expressed frustration with Aspinall's persistence in pursuing the fight, urging him to stop "whining." Despite this, the UFC includes Aspinall in their FAQ for UFC 309, suggesting that the possibility of a match between him and Jones remains open.
